            <title>[WFLY-3517] DeploymentMountProvider leaks thread pools</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-3517</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DeploymentMountProvider.start() calls Executors.newScheduledThreadPool but stop() does not shutdown the pool. The effect is the reload command results in a slow thread leak that will eventually result in OOM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
